headline: These Were the 5 Worst-Performing Stocks in the S&P 500 in January 2025
summary: The S&P 500's 2.7% rise in January might not sound impressive.  Electronic Arts' (NASDAQ: EA) stock lost 16% in January after announcing its preliminary quarterly results.  Electronic Arts produces video games for consoles, personal computers, and smartphones.
